{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d721bd6-2ed1-4760-ad93-bdc3ad9371fd","content":"Here's the plan:\n\n---\n\n## RAG Q&A Architecture for ProductQA\n\n### Overview\n\nAdd two capabilities: (1) ingest markdown docs into a vector store with chunking, and (2) a `/ask` query endpoint that retrieves relevant chunks and generates a grounded answer via an LLM.\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌────────────┐      ┌──────────────┐      ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md │─────▶│ Ingestion    │─────▶│ Vector Store   │\n└────────────┘      │ (chunk+embed)│      │ (in-memory or  │\n                    └──────────────┘      │  external)     │\n                                          └───────┬────────┘\n                                                  │ similarity search\n┌────────────┐      ┌──────────────┐              │\n│  User Q    │─────▶│ /api/ask     │──────────────┘\n└────────────┘      │ retrieve +   │      ┌────────────────┐\n                    │ generate     │─────▶│ LLM (OpenAI /  │\n                    └──────────────┘      │ Azure OpenAI)  │\n                                          └────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n| Concern | Recommendation |\n|---------|---------------|\n| **Embeddings** | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` + OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` |\n| **Vector store** | Start with `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` in-memory provider; swap to Qdrant/Azure AI Search later |\n| **Chunking** | Split by markdown heading (H1/H2), with a max token window (~500 tokens) and overlap (~50 tokens) |\n| **LLM generation** | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` chat client → OpenAI `gpt-4o` |\n| **Ingestion trigger** | `POST /api/ingest` endpoint (or startup background service) |\n\n### Proposed Project Structure\n\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Services/\n│   ├── DocumentChunker.cs      # Markdown → chunks\n│   ├── EmbeddingService.cs     # Chunks → vectors\n│   └── VectorStoreService.cs   # Store/query embeddings\n├── Controllers/\n│   ├── IngestController.cs     # POST /api/ingest\n│   └── AskController.cs        # POST /api/ask\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs        # id, text, source, embedding\n│   └── AskRequest/Response.cs\n├── Docs/                        # Existing markdown files\n├── Program.cs                   # DI registration\n└── ProductQA.csproj             # + NuGet refs\n```\n\n### NuGet Packages Needed\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI`\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.Abstractions`\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.InMemory`\n\n### Endpoint Contracts\n\n**POST /api/ingest** — scans `Docs/`, chunks, embeds, stores. Returns `{ chunksIndexed: N }`.\n\n**POST /api/ask** — body: `{ \"question\": \"...\" }` → response: `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [\"configuration.md#L1-3\"] }`.\n\n### Pipeline Flow (Query)\n\n1. Embed the user's question.\n2. Vector similarity search → top-K chunks (K=3–5).\n3. Build a system prompt: *\"Answer using only the provided context.\"*\n4. Send context + question to LLM.\n5. Return answer + source references.\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dee5a88f-cad1-4607-b48c-bc19e82f499d","outputTokens":919,"requestId":"2018:52A37:88394B:9C8662:6A05316B"},"id":"fff11b0d-13de-4223-8bb1-5c6e50af1902","timestamp":"2026-05-14T02:20:47.555Z","parentId":"5e2a3954-3024-4136-a0f0-bd0d4fb7f977"}
